---
import Docs from '../../layouts/Docs.astro';
import { keys } from '../../lib/keybindings';

const toc = [
  { id: 'splitting', text: 'Splitting', level: 2 },
  { id: 'navigation', text: 'Navigation', level: 2 },
  { id: 'resizing', text: 'Resizing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'zoom', text: 'Zoom', level: 2 },
  { id: 'floating', text: 'Floating Panes', level: 2 },
  { id: 'history', text: 'Undo / Redo', level: 2 },
  { id: 'closing', text: 'Closing', level: 2 },
];
---

<Docs title="Panes & Splits" toc={toc}>
  <h2 id="splitting">Splitting</h2>
  <p>Split the focused pane into two:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><kbd>{keys.splitRight}</kbd> — Split right (vertical divider)</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.splitDown}</kbd> — Split down (horizontal divider)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>New panes inherit the working directory of the pane they were split from. Splits can be nested to any depth.</p>

  <h2 id="navigation">Navigation</h2>
  <p>Move focus between panes spatially:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><kbd>{keys.focusLeft}</kbd> / <kbd>{keys.focusRight}</kbd> / <kbd>{keys.focusUp}</kbd> / <kbd>{keys.focusDown}</kbd> — Focus by direction</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The focused pane has an accent-colored border. Unfocused panes are dimmed slightly.</p>

  <h2 id="resizing">Resizing</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><kbd>{keys.resizePane}</kbd> — Resize the focused pane in a direction</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.equalizePanes}</kbd> — Equalize all pane sizes</li>
    <li><strong>Mouse drag</strong> — Drag any divider to resize</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Content reflows to fit the new pane size as you resize.</p>

  <h2 id="zoom">Zoom</h2>
  <p>Press <kbd>{keys.zoomPane}</kbd> to zoom the focused pane to fill the entire tab. Press again to unzoom and return to the split layout. While zoomed, all other panes are hidden but remain running.</p>

  <h2 id="floating">Floating Panes</h2>
  <p>Floating panes overlay the split tree. They can be dragged, resized, and stacked:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><kbd>{keys.toggleFloating}</kbd> — Create or toggle a floating pane</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.floatTileToggle}</kbd> — Move the focused pane between floating and tiled</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Floating panes snap to edges and enforce minimum dimensions. They have proper z-ordering — click a floating pane to raise it.</p>

  <h2 id="history">Undo / Redo</h2>
  <p>Every split, close, and layout change is recorded:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><kbd>{keys.undoSplit}</kbd> — Undo the last layout change</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.redoSplit}</kbd> — Redo</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The full history of split tree states is preserved for the session lifetime.</p>

  <h2 id="closing">Closing</h2>
  <p><kbd>{keys.closePane}</kbd> closes the focused pane. The split tree collapses automatically — the remaining panes expand to fill the space. If it's the last pane in a tab, the tab closes.</p>
</Docs>
